WEBVTT

00:01.002 --> 00:02.788
-I was not a murderer, Sarah!
-No!

00:02.795 --> 00:04.080
Not until you made me one!

00:04.088 --> 00:04.838
ANNOUNCER:
Previously on "Slasher".

00:05.006 --> 00:05.495
[ Screaming ]

00:05.715 --> 00:07.171
VAUGHN: Help me!

00:07.425 --> 00:09.461
[ Sobbing ]

00:09.469 --> 00:10.629
I love you.

00:11.137 --> 00:12.252
I'd like a memento.

00:12.638 --> 00:14.174
What kind of memento?

00:14.640 --> 00:16.972
He said he'd do it.
For a lock of my hair.

00:18.394 --> 00:19.349
That's creepy.

00:24.108 --> 00:25.848
Can I ask you why
you want that?

00:26.152 --> 00:28.108
How much does Sarah know?

00:28.362 --> 00:29.317
Dylan.

00:29.697 --> 00:31.653
Those texts were personal,
not news.

00:31.824 --> 00:33.280
-Sarah, I--
-Did you think about Cam?

00:33.284 --> 00:34.399
Did you think about
what it'll be like for him

00:34.410 --> 00:35.445
when the whole town
reads this crap?

00:35.620 --> 00:39.204
Listen, I report the news,
good or bad. You know that.

00:40.291 --> 00:41.576
Oh, my God.

00:42.043 --> 00:44.580
Is-- Is that Tom?

00:45.338 --> 00:46.327
You're not my father.

00:46.714 --> 00:48.329
Sarah, it's not a matter
of thinking anything.

00:48.341 --> 00:49.126
Reading, huh?

00:49.800 --> 00:50.585
[ Groaning ]

00:51.761 --> 00:52.546
[Yelling ]

01:00.478 --> 01:01.513
TOM: Sarah.

01:02.522 --> 01:03.557
-Hey.
-[ Groans]

01:03.731 --> 01:05.562
Take it easy.
Take it easy!

01:08.277 --> 01:10.142
Did they call you?

01:11.030 --> 01:12.236
SARAH: No.

01:12.406 --> 01:13.441
I came myself.

01:13.616 --> 01:14.605
[ Tom sighs ]

01:16.911 --> 01:18.026
SARAH: How you feeling?

01:18.496 --> 01:19.451
[ Snickers ]

01:19.956 --> 01:21.162
How am I feeling?

01:21.499 --> 01:23.990
[ Inhales deeply ]

01:24.335 --> 01:25.745
You came to see me.

01:28.172 --> 01:29.332
Yeah.

01:30.508 --> 01:32.248
Had a lot of time to think.

01:32.760 --> 01:34.591
Put things into perspective
and...

01:36.055 --> 01:37.511
What?

01:39.225 --> 01:42.058
I don't have enough family left
to pick and choose. So...

01:43.396 --> 01:44.886
SARAH: If we're gonna do this...

01:46.107 --> 01:47.688
there's gonna be
some ground rules.

01:48.150 --> 01:49.606
Anything.

01:53.489 --> 01:54.945
No more lies.

01:57.827 --> 01:59.863
No more lies.

02:02.415 --> 02:03.996
I promise.

02:05.668 --> 02:07.329
What do you want to know?

02:09.547 --> 02:11.959
I wanna know
why you killed my...

02:13.634 --> 02:15.875
my mother and her husband.

02:18.723 --> 02:20.714
I want you to tell me the truth.

02:21.601 --> 02:24.308
I want you to tell me...
everything.

02:24.520 --> 02:25.976
Every detail.

02:26.564 --> 02:28.179
From the beginning.

02:35.281 --> 02:36.987
CHILDREN: Trick or treat!

02:37.199 --> 02:38.700
WOMAN: Stop running!

02:41.203 --> 02:43.285
CHILDREN: Trick or treat!

02:47.668 --> 02:49.499
[ Kids screaming ]

02:52.256 --> 02:53.917
[ Screaming continues ]

02:54.300 --> 02:55.756
[ Heavy breathing ]

02:58.638 --> 03:00.424
[ Heavy breathing continues ]

03:00.598 --> 03:02.429
[ Kids screaming ]

03:13.444 --> 03:15.184
Lose the scarf.
You look like Liberace.

03:15.613 --> 03:16.648
No, I don't.
I look cool.

03:16.656 --> 03:17.771
[ Woman laughs ]

03:20.284 --> 03:22.275
[ Doorbell rings ]

03:22.703 --> 03:25.035
Hey, hon.
I think that's Alan.

03:25.206 --> 03:26.946
We'll have a beer here first,
and then we'll go, okay?

03:27.124 --> 03:28.660
WOMAN:
Sounds good.

03:30.670 --> 03:32.251
Thought you guys were going
trick-or-treating as, uh...

03:32.588 --> 03:34.544
King Arthur and his band
of Merry Men.

03:34.757 --> 03:36.167
Wait, that's Robin Hood, right?

03:36.592 --> 03:38.048
Anyway, man,
Rachel's bailing.

03:38.052 --> 03:40.168
Yeah, this last trimester
is killing her.

03:40.388 --> 03:41.343
MAN: I can't remember,

03:41.347 --> 03:42.883
was the last trimester
like that for Suzy?

03:42.890 --> 03:44.755
Tired all the time.
Not sleepin'.

03:47.395 --> 03:48.305
[ Heavy breathing ]

03:48.854 --> 03:51.061
Hey, Al, you want to take
that stupid mask off now?

03:51.315 --> 03:52.395
[ Heavy breathing continues ]

03:53.109 --> 03:54.269
Have a seat, man.

03:54.276 --> 03:55.402
I'll get us a beer
or something, okay?

03:55.903 --> 03:56.813
[ Doorbell rings ]

03:57.446 --> 03:58.356
Here.

03:58.364 --> 03:59.900
Hand these out for me?

03:59.907 --> 04:00.817
[ Heavy breathing ]

04:01.325 --> 04:02.656
No?

04:03.703 --> 04:04.488
[ Snickers ]

04:05.830 --> 04:07.411
Thanks for your help.

04:13.754 --> 04:15.494
-[ Door opening ]
-MAN: Happy Halloween!

04:15.673 --> 04:16.458
MAN: 50...

04:16.757 --> 04:17.667
What do you think?

04:18.134 --> 04:19.795
Pretty good, huh?

04:20.219 --> 04:22.210
Oh, and you should see
Suzie's "Guinevere".

04:22.430 --> 04:24.045
I fell in love with her
all over again.

04:24.640 --> 04:26.176
Hey, check it out.

04:27.476 --> 04:28.807
How cute is that?

04:29.103 --> 04:31.469
Does Cam look like
a tiny little Merlin or what?

04:31.480 --> 04:32.265
[ Laughs ]

04:33.399 --> 04:34.809
Alan, what the hell's
going on here?

04:35.776 --> 04:36.731
Who's that?

04:40.823 --> 04:42.063
I-- I thought that was you.

04:43.951 --> 04:44.736
[ Gasps ]

04:45.119 --> 04:46.359
[ Screaming ]

04:50.040 --> 04:51.325
[ Screaming continues ]

04:52.877 --> 04:54.287
[ Screaming ]

04:57.173 --> 04:58.629
[Whimpering ]
Please. Please.

04:58.883 --> 04:59.713
[ Groaning ]

04:59.884 --> 05:00.919
[ Screaming ]

05:17.151 --> 05:18.391
[ Screaming ]

05:20.946 --> 05:22.607
[ Sobbing ]

05:24.325 --> 05:25.280
[ Screaming ]
Help!

05:25.659 --> 05:27.911
Help! Please!

05:28.829 --> 05:29.818
[ Sobbing continues]

05:34.043 --> 05:35.408
No! Please!

05:36.045 --> 05:36.830
No!

05:37.004 --> 05:38.084
Tom!

05:38.923 --> 05:40.038
No, don't!

05:40.049 --> 05:40.959
Don't!

05:40.966 --> 05:42.502
Don't kill our baby!
Please!

05:42.843 --> 05:43.628
Please.

05:43.928 --> 05:45.668
[ Crying ]
It's yours!

05:47.515 --> 05:49.051
She is.

05:50.142 --> 05:51.928
I wanted to tell you...

05:52.770 --> 05:55.056
but Bryan said he would
kill me if I ever left him.

05:55.064 --> 05:56.645
Kill me and the baby.

05:57.024 --> 05:57.934
Please!

05:58.734 --> 05:59.894
I love you.

06:01.570 --> 06:02.525
[ Crying ]
I love you.

06:02.905 --> 06:04.520
I didn't mean to fall in love
with you.

06:04.532 --> 06:05.988
But I did.

06:05.991 --> 06:06.946
I swear!

06:07.618 --> 06:08.607
I love you.

06:08.869 --> 06:09.654
[ Gasping ]

06:10.579 --> 06:11.659
[ Screaming ]

06:16.377 --> 06:17.662
[ Screaming ]

06:25.678 --> 06:27.418
It was the only way
I could save you

06:27.429 --> 06:28.635
from the two of them.

06:28.639 --> 06:30.971
No. Why didn't you just call
Children's Aid

06:30.975 --> 06:32.715
or sued for custody or...?
I mean...

06:32.977 --> 06:34.467
Hell, you could have even
kidnapped me.

06:34.478 --> 06:35.228
Sarah.

06:36.856 --> 06:38.221
Tell me the truth.

06:39.525 --> 06:40.981
Why did you kill them?

06:46.991 --> 06:47.901
[ Scoffs ]

06:47.908 --> 06:49.739
Take care of yourself, Tom.

06:50.369 --> 06:51.984
[ Door opening ]

06:52.162 --> 06:53.072
[ Door closing ]

07:01.297 --> 07:02.082
[ Birds chirping ]

07:06.260 --> 07:07.591
[ Wind rustling ]

07:08.262 --> 07:09.502
Am I dumb?

07:10.556 --> 07:12.046
-What?
-Am I dumb?

07:12.600 --> 07:14.261
I was beginning to think
that moving back to Waterbury

07:14.435 --> 07:16.016
was the stupidest idea ever.

07:17.563 --> 07:20.555
Uh... Ariel Peterson is alive
because of you.

07:21.525 --> 07:23.902
That's not dumb.
That's... amazing.

07:24.987 --> 07:25.772
Honey.

07:27.239 --> 07:29.696
Tom is your father in DNA only.

07:30.659 --> 07:31.614
Okay?

07:32.953 --> 07:33.738
Hmm.

07:33.913 --> 07:34.698
Now...

07:34.955 --> 07:37.367
Eating for one is one
of the loneliest ways to eat.

07:37.583 --> 07:38.493
So...

07:38.959 --> 07:40.244
How 'bout we harden
our arteries?

07:40.419 --> 07:41.454
-My treat.
-Yeah.

07:41.629 --> 07:42.914
Yeah, I'd love to, but...

07:44.214 --> 07:45.954
Dylan and I are having a talk.

07:46.675 --> 07:47.505
Uh-oh.

07:47.968 --> 07:49.924
More trouble in paradise?

07:49.929 --> 07:52.215
No paradise, just trouble.

07:53.307 --> 07:54.888
[ Train horn ]

07:56.143 --> 07:56.928
SARAH: Dylan?

07:57.102 --> 07:57.966
DYLAN: In here.

07:59.146 --> 08:00.101
Dylan.

08:02.232 --> 08:03.187
What's all this?

08:03.984 --> 08:05.815
Well, this is a, uh,
fiddlehead salad

08:05.819 --> 08:06.854
with a little...

08:06.862 --> 08:08.818
pickled red onion
and toasted pecans,

08:09.073 --> 08:10.779
followed by a pan-seared
lamb chop,

08:10.783 --> 08:12.899
pomegranate relish,

08:12.910 --> 08:14.901
and potato gratin on the side.

08:15.204 --> 08:16.364
And to wrap it all up,

08:16.372 --> 08:20.035
we have roasted pear with
mascarpone espresso cream.

08:22.086 --> 08:23.542
Took the day off.

08:24.129 --> 08:25.585
Well, almost, kinda.

08:25.839 --> 08:27.170
I'm live with Lisa-Ann
later on,

08:27.383 --> 08:28.839
but that was scheduled
way before.

08:29.009 --> 08:30.215
Please, don't be upset.

08:31.095 --> 08:33.006
Upset? I mean,
why would I be upset?

08:33.013 --> 08:34.298
This is...

08:34.807 --> 08:36.297
I can't believe
you did all this.

08:38.060 --> 08:39.049
I've been a bad husband.

08:39.269 --> 08:40.179
No.

08:40.187 --> 08:42.178
No, I have.
And, uh....

08:42.940 --> 08:44.805
This is my way of--
of trying to...

08:45.234 --> 08:47.020
get things back on track.

08:49.029 --> 08:49.859
Thank you.

08:50.489 --> 08:52.025
To a new start.

08:52.574 --> 08:53.984
To fresh starts.

08:54.994 --> 08:58.111
DYLAN: And moving here, and this
huge change in our lives...

09:02.126 --> 09:05.084
All this attention was thrown
my way, and, uh...

09:06.380 --> 09:08.166
I wasn't ready for it.

09:09.008 --> 09:11.169
And I let it go
straight to my head.

09:12.594 --> 09:14.209
And it took, um...

09:14.596 --> 09:15.346
[ Sniffs ]

09:15.514 --> 09:17.596
It took almost losing you
to-- to realize

09:17.599 --> 09:19.851
what it was actually
doing to me.

09:21.729 --> 09:23.811
DYLAN: No, no, not to me.
That's wrong.

09:24.064 --> 09:25.520
'Cause I did this, and...

09:26.316 --> 09:27.772
'Cause I did it.

09:27.776 --> 09:29.152
I made bad choices.

09:29.319 --> 09:30.308
[ Sighs ]

09:31.071 --> 09:32.652
And I'm embarrassed, Sarah.

09:32.656 --> 09:33.406
[ Sighs ]

09:33.741 --> 09:35.277
And I'm ashamed.

09:37.870 --> 09:39.735
Dylan, how...?

09:40.456 --> 09:41.411
[ Sighs ]

09:41.415 --> 09:42.575
Neither of us
could have imagined,

09:42.583 --> 09:45.245
when we moved here,
that this would happen.

09:46.128 --> 09:48.084
You know?
We weren't prepared.

09:49.298 --> 09:51.414
How--
How could we have been?

09:54.803 --> 09:56.304
You know?

09:56.305 --> 09:58.967
Now, we...
we have to face reality.

10:02.186 --> 10:04.347
And the reality is
we can't stay here.

10:07.066 --> 10:10.024
And you can't keep
covering the story.

10:10.027 --> 10:11.608
It'll destroy us.

10:15.324 --> 10:17.815
The truth is it's...

10:18.452 --> 10:22.036
either your career
or our marriage.

10:24.875 --> 10:26.536
I don't want to lose you.

10:28.003 --> 10:30.085
I don't want
to lose you either.

10:34.426 --> 10:35.461
DISPATCH: All units,
we have a report

10:35.636 --> 10:37.922
of a possible trespass
at 35 McCall Street.

10:37.930 --> 10:41.138
The premises at that location
is abandoned. Over.

10:43.352 --> 10:44.432
[ Gasps ]

10:52.069 --> 10:52.854
Dispatch!

10:53.237 --> 10:55.319
3-2-0-5 on the scene
at 35 McCall.

10:55.322 --> 10:56.653
I'm out of the car,
checking out the premises.

10:56.990 --> 10:57.900
Over.

10:57.908 --> 10:58.943
DISPATCH: Copy that.

11:01.495 --> 11:03.406
[ Floor creaking ]

11:20.973 --> 11:22.338
What the hell?

11:29.731 --> 11:30.766
[ Floor creaking ]

11:32.067 --> 11:33.056
Police!

11:33.235 --> 11:34.065
Come out!

11:34.319 --> 11:36.310
[ Panting ]

11:40.325 --> 11:41.610
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

11:41.827 --> 11:43.658
-Easy, Sharma!
-SHARMA: Holy shit, Cam.

11:44.288 --> 11:45.528
Check it out.

11:49.042 --> 11:50.327
Jesus.

11:55.215 --> 11:59.834
SHARMA: Wrath, gluttony,
envy, lust, greed, sloth?

12:00.679 --> 12:02.135
Aren't there seven deadly sins?

12:02.139 --> 12:03.424
I'm only counting six.

12:04.057 --> 12:04.921
Yeah.

12:05.601 --> 12:06.886
Pride.

12:08.478 --> 12:10.093
Hadn't been put up yet.

12:17.863 --> 12:19.148
SHARMA: This is
where the Vickers family died...

12:20.157 --> 12:21.943
that winter
a couple of years ago.

12:22.326 --> 12:23.816
Suffocated.

12:24.828 --> 12:25.943
CAM: Yeah.

12:26.455 --> 12:28.537
Youngest kid
was only 8-years-old.

12:29.374 --> 12:30.580
[ Sighs ]

12:31.543 --> 12:32.828
CAM: You go
through any of this?

12:33.086 --> 12:33.996
No.

12:45.974 --> 12:47.555
CAM: Verna McBride.

12:51.355 --> 12:52.845
Justin Faysal.

12:55.317 --> 12:56.306
Brenda Merritt.

12:56.568 --> 12:57.899
Envy.

13:00.489 --> 13:02.775
Trent McBride, June Henry.

13:06.453 --> 13:08.114
Iain Vaughn.

13:13.418 --> 13:14.624
Oh, Jesus.

13:15.295 --> 13:17.001
Sarah.

13:18.882 --> 13:19.746
Dispatch.

13:19.925 --> 13:20.914
DISPATCH: Go ahead.

13:20.926 --> 13:22.462
I need forensics
at 35 McCall Street.

13:22.636 --> 13:23.546
-DISPATCH: Copy.
-I want you to oversee

13:23.553 --> 13:25.168
the transfer of Tom Winston
back to Franklin Penitentiary.

13:25.180 --> 13:26.386
You hear me?

13:26.390 --> 13:27.630
Right.
I'm going to get Sarah.

13:27.891 --> 13:28.880
[ Softly ]
Come back.

13:30.227 --> 13:32.138
[ Scrubbing dishes ]

13:32.437 --> 13:34.052
Oh. Oh, oh...
Let me get that.

13:34.231 --> 13:35.095
Let me get that.

13:35.274 --> 13:36.309
I can help.

13:36.483 --> 13:38.269
No, you can go and rest...

13:39.027 --> 13:41.188
...your leg,
is what you can do.

13:43.907 --> 13:45.192
Yeah?

13:45.200 --> 13:46.940
I'll join you
when I'm done in here.

13:47.160 --> 13:48.115
Mmm.

13:48.120 --> 13:49.405
Sounds good.

13:50.998 --> 13:53.080
[ Scrubbing dishes ]

14:02.259 --> 14:03.669
[ Sighs ]

14:14.313 --> 14:15.098
Dylan?

14:15.439 --> 14:17.145
DYLAN: Hmm?

14:18.191 --> 14:19.567
Dylan, I know
you've been focusing

14:19.568 --> 14:21.479
on the present-day
killings, but...

14:21.903 --> 14:22.983
you haven't come across
anything new

14:22.988 --> 14:24.774
about my parents, have you?

14:29.328 --> 14:30.864
SARAH: Dylan?

14:31.580 --> 14:33.912
Yeah, sorry, I was just
putting something away.

14:34.082 --> 14:34.912
Umm...

14:35.250 --> 14:36.456
Anything new, like what?

14:37.044 --> 14:38.454
I don't know, actu...

14:39.129 --> 14:41.211
I just get the feeling that Tom
isn't telling me everything.

14:42.424 --> 14:44.130
Yeah?
You think he, uh...

14:44.384 --> 14:45.544
he's holding
something back?

14:46.511 --> 14:47.717
Maybe.

14:48.263 --> 14:51.346
DYLAN: Well, you know, um,
nothing comes to mind, but...

14:51.516 --> 14:53.017
you know, I haven't
really been looking.

14:54.269 --> 14:55.384
Well, okay.

14:55.854 --> 14:57.014
No problem.

14:58.398 --> 14:59.478
Okay.

15:18.960 --> 15:20.211
[ Faucet running ]

15:22.130 --> 15:23.961
[ Dishes clinking ]

15:39.606 --> 15:41.392
[ Phone vibrating ]

15:54.329 --> 15:56.285
[ Phone vibrating ]

16:06.466 --> 16:08.081
[ Phone vibrating ]

16:24.943 --> 16:26.524
Dylan, what's your password?

16:26.820 --> 16:29.061
7438. Why?

16:30.449 --> 16:32.565
Wi-Fi's spotty, and I want
to Google something.

16:33.702 --> 16:34.862
Hey.

16:34.870 --> 16:35.905
So I was thinking.

16:36.246 --> 16:38.237
Tom Winston...
has a huge ego, right?

16:38.582 --> 16:41.289
If he's hiding something,
if he's holding something back,

16:41.293 --> 16:43.579
maybe... you should play him.

16:43.879 --> 16:45.665
Make him think
that it was his idea

16:45.672 --> 16:47.833
to come out and give
the whole story.

16:47.841 --> 16:49.706
You know what I mean?
That might-- that might work.

16:49.718 --> 16:51.049
Give it a shot, at least.

16:51.303 --> 16:52.167
SARAH: I don't know.

16:53.346 --> 16:54.961
Why don't we ask you?

16:56.141 --> 16:57.677
You're the expert.

16:59.728 --> 17:01.434
I found your website.

17:06.026 --> 17:07.687
Okay, Sarah, listen. Um...

17:07.694 --> 17:09.025
What?

17:09.654 --> 17:10.689
What are you gonna say?

17:10.697 --> 17:11.482
Okay, look...

17:11.698 --> 17:13.063
I've-- I've--
I've been following

17:13.074 --> 17:14.575
the Executioner's story
for a while.

17:14.743 --> 17:15.858
You certainly did.

17:15.869 --> 17:16.858
But when I fell in love
with you,

17:16.870 --> 17:18.110
it was not because of the story.

17:19.498 --> 17:20.487
I swear to God.

17:20.499 --> 17:22.035
I fell in love with you
because I fell...

17:22.042 --> 17:23.623
in love... with you.

17:24.002 --> 17:24.752
Sarah.

17:24.920 --> 17:26.080
When we met?

17:27.464 --> 17:29.125
You were looking for me.
You were looking for a lead!

17:29.299 --> 17:31.540
That all went away,
once I got to know you.

17:31.551 --> 17:32.711
-You have to understand that.
-SARAH: No. No.

17:32.928 --> 17:33.883
Oh, my God.
Everything you said.

17:34.095 --> 17:35.084
Everything you said
was a lie!

17:35.347 --> 17:36.177
[ Banging on door ]

17:36.640 --> 17:37.595
Leave us alone, okay?

17:37.849 --> 17:39.134
Don't touch me!

17:39.142 --> 17:40.302
-Talk to me. Goddamnit!
-No!

17:41.061 --> 17:41.891
Leave!

17:44.147 --> 17:45.353
-Cam.
-DYLAN: Hey, man.

17:46.107 --> 17:47.563
Cam, what are you doing?

17:48.777 --> 17:50.313
It's The Executioner.

17:51.696 --> 17:53.027
He's coming for you.

17:58.286 --> 17:59.321
CAM: We still
haven't ruled Dylan out

17:59.329 --> 18:00.569
as a suspect, Sarah.

18:00.580 --> 18:02.081
He's gonna have to stay
somewhere else tonight.

18:02.249 --> 18:03.785
Yeah, that's fine.
I don't want him here.

18:04.125 --> 18:05.911
Uh, Cam, I am such an idiot.

18:06.670 --> 18:08.126
How are you supposed
to know, Sarah?

18:08.421 --> 18:09.797
You had your doubts.

18:10.048 --> 18:11.163
Why couldn't I see
what you could?

18:13.301 --> 18:14.632
Oh, come on.

18:15.220 --> 18:17.085
Don't beat yourself up
about it.

18:17.639 --> 18:20.221
Dylan's actions were his
and his alone.

18:21.518 --> 18:24.260
Did you ever find it
in your heart to forgive June?

18:24.479 --> 18:26.640
[ Crickets chirping ]

18:27.357 --> 18:28.187
SARAH: Sorry.

18:28.817 --> 18:30.603
I'm sorry.
None of my business.

18:30.610 --> 18:32.020
No, no, no. Um...

18:33.572 --> 18:35.108
[ Sighs ]

18:36.283 --> 18:37.739
June hurt me.

18:38.785 --> 18:39.865
Badly.

18:42.372 --> 18:44.533
Yeah, I tried to forgive her,
but...

18:45.125 --> 18:45.910
[ Sighs ]

18:46.543 --> 18:48.750
I think if I'm being completely
honest with myself...

18:50.547 --> 18:51.332
No.

18:51.756 --> 18:54.247
[ Crickets chirping ]

18:55.969 --> 18:57.630
[ Cam clears throat ]

18:58.305 --> 18:59.545
CAM: Hey.

19:00.223 --> 19:03.260
Why don't you head upstairs
and get yourself some sleep?

19:06.396 --> 19:07.181
Yeah?

19:07.439 --> 19:09.100
Yeah, I'll try.

19:16.031 --> 19:18.943
Seven sins, six killings.

19:18.950 --> 19:21.066
Only one victim remains.

19:21.244 --> 19:23.109
Who is that unlucky soul?

19:23.288 --> 19:25.574
And will the police
find him or her

19:25.790 --> 19:27.621
before The Executioner does?

19:27.959 --> 19:30.575
LISA-ANN: It's a race against
time here in Waterbury.

19:30.587 --> 19:34.830
A town on edge and waiting
for the killer to strike again.

19:35.383 --> 19:36.884
LISA-ANN: I'm here
with Dylan Bennett,

19:37.135 --> 19:39.251
Editor—in—Chief
and acting publisher

19:39.262 --> 19:40.422
of the Waterbury Bulletin.

19:40.680 --> 19:41.886
Dylan...

19:41.890 --> 19:43.255
I've heard reports,

19:43.266 --> 19:45.131
the police have
discovered a kill list.

19:45.393 --> 19:46.508
That is correct, Lisa-Ann.
Yes.

19:46.853 --> 19:48.138
Any idea,
who's on that list?

19:48.396 --> 19:50.648
The police are keeping all that
information to themselves.

19:51.024 --> 19:54.516
My sources tell me that
Tom Winston made the cut.

19:54.527 --> 19:56.313
As did your wife,
Sarah Bennett.

19:56.905 --> 19:58.361
LISA-ANN: Is that true?

19:58.907 --> 20:00.272
Lisa-Ann, um...

20:01.660 --> 20:04.697
I-- I can't comment...
on that, at this time.

20:04.704 --> 20:06.865
Well, assuming my information
is correct,

20:07.165 --> 20:10.578
can you think of any reason
why Sarah would be a target?

20:10.835 --> 20:12.575
Tom Winston is a murderer,

20:13.254 --> 20:15.245
but what did Sarah do...

20:15.507 --> 20:17.714
to be
on The Executioner's radar?

20:20.345 --> 20:22.176
Why don't we talk
about what we do know?

20:23.098 --> 20:25.009
That the one outstanding sin
is pride.

20:25.433 --> 20:28.596
And as you may
or may not know, Lisa-Ann,

20:28.770 --> 20:30.556
pride is the cardinal sin.

20:31.356 --> 20:32.812
The most serious sin

20:32.816 --> 20:35.182
because it steals away
from God's righteous glory.

20:35.777 --> 20:38.063
[ Car accelerating ]

20:38.530 --> 20:40.737
[Siren wailing ]

20:43.368 --> 20:45.780
This must be a lot more exciting
than your usual milk run, huh?

20:46.037 --> 20:47.277
What's going on, anyway?

20:47.455 --> 20:48.740
Everyone's so on edge.

20:48.957 --> 20:50.117
Is it The Executioner?

20:50.583 --> 20:52.619
SHARMA: I discovered
who the final victims are.

20:52.794 --> 20:54.159
Sarah Bennett and...

20:57.090 --> 20:58.330
You see,

20:58.341 --> 20:59.751
there comes a time
in every officer's life

20:59.759 --> 21:00.999
where he has to...

21:01.010 --> 21:03.092
come up against something.

21:03.346 --> 21:04.426
Something dangerous.

21:04.431 --> 21:06.342
Something where only
the greatest can move forward.

21:06.349 --> 21:07.099
[ Groaning ]

21:07.267 --> 21:09.223
Something that's gonna
define my career as an officer.

21:09.477 --> 21:10.933
It's gonna keep this town safe.

21:11.104 --> 21:12.594
My handcuffs are too tight.

21:12.897 --> 21:14.012
SHARMA:
I'm sorry, what?

21:14.357 --> 21:16.097
Cutting off the circulation
in my hands.

21:16.276 --> 21:17.436
I expect better treatment
than this.

21:17.610 --> 21:20.602
You think I feel sorry for you
after what you did, you monster?

21:20.613 --> 21:22.319
It's okay. I got this.

21:22.574 --> 21:23.359
Now, Tom...

21:23.533 --> 21:25.398
Take it easy.
You had a bad concussion.

21:25.577 --> 21:26.817
Why don't you just sit back

21:26.828 --> 21:29.114
and enjoy some
of that sweet wat...

21:29.330 --> 21:30.706
[ Choking ]

21:32.959 --> 21:34.199
[ Screaming ]

21:36.087 --> 21:37.247
[ Continues screaming ]

21:38.089 --> 21:39.625
Tom! Stop!

21:45.597 --> 21:46.928
PARAMEDIC: No.

21:49.392 --> 21:50.973
To answer your question,

21:50.977 --> 21:53.764
no, I don't expect you
to feel sorry for me.

21:53.772 --> 21:55.854
'Cause I sure as hell
don't feel sorry for you.

21:56.149 --> 21:56.934
No!

21:57.150 --> 21:57.980
[ Screaming ]

21:58.693 --> 21:59.603
PARAMEDIC: Stop!

21:59.611 --> 22:01.522
-TOM: Say it again!
-PARAMEDIC: Stop!

22:07.118 --> 22:09.825
LISA-ANN: Now,
before you get all angry

22:10.747 --> 22:12.578
and accuse me
of ambushing you...

22:12.582 --> 22:14.118
In my defense...

22:14.709 --> 22:17.792
you kept a pretty key piece
of evidence from me tonight.

22:18.338 --> 22:21.922
Maybe the fact that...
my wife is on the kill list?

22:22.091 --> 22:24.503
Yeah, I can't imagine why
I'd want to keep that to myself.

22:24.511 --> 22:25.921
It's news.

22:26.137 --> 22:27.877
I mean, it's horrible news,

22:27.889 --> 22:30.676
and I hope it all works out,
but this is what we do.

22:30.683 --> 22:31.718
Excuse me.

22:31.726 --> 22:34.012
Uh, Sauvignon blanc for me and...

22:34.437 --> 22:35.643
whatever my friend here
is drinking.

22:35.980 --> 22:37.060
Thanks.

22:38.233 --> 22:41.316
So the next time something
like this happens...

22:41.778 --> 22:44.440
...all you gotta do is be
open and honest with me.

22:44.447 --> 22:45.687
That way we can work together.

22:46.115 --> 22:49.403
Instead of me getting
all vindictive and pissed off.

22:49.953 --> 22:51.284
And territorial.

22:52.121 --> 22:53.372
Make sense?

22:55.291 --> 22:57.543
Not a lot makes sense
anymore.

23:05.552 --> 23:08.885
My first husband was killed
in a drive-by shooting.

23:11.140 --> 23:12.846
Wrong place at the wrong time.

23:15.061 --> 23:16.471
I warned him.

23:17.605 --> 23:19.186
But more importantly...

23:19.691 --> 23:22.728
I leveraged his death
to get to where I am today.

23:24.028 --> 23:26.861
The fearless defender
of the little guy.

23:27.991 --> 23:30.949
Now his parents and friends
hate me, but...

23:31.160 --> 23:32.195
You know what?

23:32.954 --> 23:35.366
They live in a shitty suburb
in Philadelphia,

23:35.874 --> 23:38.115
and I live
in a 5,000-square foot condo

23:38.126 --> 23:39.536
in Central Park West.

23:40.879 --> 23:43.086
This book will put you
on the map.

23:43.298 --> 23:44.629
But everything's got its price.

23:48.636 --> 23:49.796
What book?

23:50.972 --> 23:52.553
Well, I soft pitched
your book idea

23:52.557 --> 23:53.922
to my publishers
this afternoon.

23:54.100 --> 23:55.510
And they ate it up.

23:55.768 --> 23:57.804
Contracts are being drawn up
as we speak.

23:58.897 --> 23:59.886
So is this happening?

24:00.148 --> 24:02.104
[ Laughs ]
LISA-ANN: This is happening.

24:02.442 --> 24:03.352
Yeah.

24:06.195 --> 24:08.231
So stop being
all broody and angry.

24:10.199 --> 24:11.985
And drink with me.

24:20.627 --> 24:21.867
If I 'm being honest,

24:21.878 --> 24:23.493
every problem I 've had
is that bitch 's fault.

24:23.838 --> 24:25.578
MAN: You gotta stop letting
Amy mess with you.

24:25.757 --> 24:27.213
WOMAN: But she just
doesn't get it.

24:27.425 --> 24:28.790
You're my husband.

24:29.677 --> 24:31.713
SHARMA: Chief Henry?
Come in.

24:32.722 --> 24:33.962
What's going on, Sharma?

24:34.265 --> 24:37.052
SHARMA: Be on the lookout
for Tom Winston.

24:37.226 --> 24:40.093
Tom Winston
has escaped our custody.

24:40.605 --> 24:41.890
What the hell are you
talking about, Sharma?

24:42.607 --> 24:44.268
Never mind. Just meet me
at the station with Sarah.

24:44.442 --> 24:46.057
Did I hear that right?
Tom's escaped?

24:46.069 --> 24:47.024
Yeah, come on.

24:47.028 --> 24:47.392
We gotta get you
somewhere secure.

24:47.570 --> 24:49.071
Right now.

24:49.072 --> 24:50.107
TOM: Sarah.

24:51.032 --> 24:52.021
Sarah, go back upstairs.

24:52.367 --> 24:53.732
You sure about that, sport?

24:53.993 --> 24:55.858
She's the only thing stopping me
from shooting you.

24:56.788 --> 24:58.449
Let me have the gun.
Real slow.

24:58.790 --> 24:59.950
Let's have it!

25:02.585 --> 25:03.620
What do you want, Tom?

25:03.878 --> 25:06.244
I want you to come with me.
So I can protect you.

25:06.923 --> 25:07.878
Cam's protecting me.

25:08.132 --> 25:09.508
And he's doing
such a bang-up job.

25:10.677 --> 25:12.417
You're not safe, Sarah.
Not in this house.

25:12.720 --> 25:14.096
So please.
Come with me.

25:14.389 --> 25:15.299
I'm not letting you
walk out of here.

25:15.807 --> 25:16.762
What's the alternative?

25:17.058 --> 25:18.798
I won't hurt her.
You have my word.

25:19.602 --> 25:20.887
Your word's not worth shit.

25:21.688 --> 25:22.848
He won't, Cam.

25:23.272 --> 25:24.057
Trust me.

25:24.774 --> 25:25.809
Trust you?

25:27.735 --> 25:29.020
Tom is my father.

25:29.696 --> 25:31.357
SARAH: I wouldn't lie
about something like this.

25:31.948 --> 25:33.313
TOM: Over...

25:33.700 --> 25:35.361
Let's go! Come on!

25:37.120 --> 25:38.576
You don't know, bitch...

25:42.792 --> 25:44.703
Get down
on your goddamn knees!

25:45.336 --> 25:46.166
Cuff yourself.

25:52.719 --> 25:54.209
[ Cuffs snapping ]

25:54.762 --> 25:55.547
Radio.

26:02.854 --> 26:03.934
Car keys.

26:04.522 --> 26:05.386
[ Sighs ]

26:05.398 --> 26:07.354
-You gotta be kidding me
-Where are they?

26:07.567 --> 26:08.397
[ Sighs ]

26:09.193 --> 26:10.603
They're by the door.

26:11.821 --> 26:12.981
All right, then.

26:14.157 --> 26:15.522
[ Sighs ]

26:21.789 --> 26:22.904
Let's go.

26:27.378 --> 26:29.118
[ Panting ]

26:32.341 --> 26:33.751
SARAH: We shouldn't be
out here, Tom.

26:34.761 --> 26:35.750
You're injured.

26:36.054 --> 26:37.885
Don't worry about me.
I'm fine.

26:38.181 --> 26:40.137
[ Raining ]

26:45.688 --> 26:46.438
[ Groans]

26:47.148 --> 26:49.309
So you still don't trust me,
huh?

26:49.567 --> 26:50.352
Oh, I trust you.

26:50.860 --> 26:52.350
It's everybody else
I got a problem with.

26:54.280 --> 26:55.110
[ Sniffs ]

26:55.656 --> 26:57.317
I mean it, Tom.

26:58.826 --> 27:00.282
You're gonna end up
back in prison.

27:00.453 --> 27:01.738
Worse.

27:02.705 --> 27:04.787
You still don't understand,
do you?

27:05.124 --> 27:06.409
Understand what?

27:07.293 --> 27:09.329
I'd rather die than lose you.

27:14.467 --> 27:17.004
[ Struggling ]

27:34.403 --> 27:35.904
[ Panting ]

27:40.952 --> 27:42.817
[ Door opening ]

27:50.086 --> 27:51.246
[ Softly ]
Oh, Sharma.

27:52.088 --> 27:53.669
You're handcuffed?

27:54.298 --> 27:55.708
You get strangled?

27:55.967 --> 27:56.797
Again?

27:58.511 --> 27:59.296
Yeah.

28:00.471 --> 28:01.847
Come on, get me out of here.

28:05.434 --> 28:08.722
So, we were doing this exposé
on youth drug addiction.

28:08.729 --> 28:09.889
Mm-hm.

28:09.897 --> 28:10.852
And this kid we lined up...

28:11.023 --> 28:13.981
He was an addict,
supposed to be.

28:13.985 --> 28:15.771
But he hadn't used
in a couple of days.

28:16.696 --> 28:19.859
There's no drama...
in a clean meth head.

28:20.283 --> 28:22.023
So, I...

28:22.326 --> 28:24.442
got my assistant
to score him some "ice".

28:24.453 --> 28:25.704
No.

28:26.205 --> 28:28.287
And I got nominated
for a Peabody.

28:28.499 --> 28:29.329
Oh!

28:30.168 --> 28:31.248
That's bad.

28:31.502 --> 28:33.584
I mean, that's not
"use your wife for a story,"

28:33.588 --> 28:35.419
but that's... pretty bad.

28:35.673 --> 28:36.833
Okay. All right.

28:36.841 --> 28:38.422
Enough
with the self-flagellation.

28:38.426 --> 28:39.336
DYLAN: Mmm.

28:39.343 --> 28:43.086
Gone from being pretty pathetic
to downright boring.

28:44.932 --> 28:46.763
Oh, you think they want us
out of here?

28:47.894 --> 28:48.679
Yeah.

28:48.895 --> 28:50.977
Yeah, it's about that time,
but I'm not boring.

28:51.147 --> 28:51.932
-[ Laughs]
-I'm...

28:52.148 --> 28:53.684
Mr. Fun.
They call me Mr. Fun.

28:54.525 --> 28:55.480
You are boring.

28:56.068 --> 28:56.853
You know why?

28:57.028 --> 28:58.234
You lied to Sarah.

28:59.238 --> 29:00.193
Big whoop.

29:00.740 --> 29:03.857
Now, if she can't see
past your betrayal or...

29:04.410 --> 29:05.570
your mistake...

29:06.287 --> 29:08.573
Then maybe you two
aren't as in love

29:08.581 --> 29:09.912
as you thought you were.

29:10.791 --> 29:11.655
But what do I know?

29:12.126 --> 29:13.457
What do I know?

29:13.753 --> 29:15.368
In vino veritas.

29:15.922 --> 29:17.458
And I have certainly had
a lot to drink.

29:17.465 --> 29:18.545
-[ Laughs ]
-You have had a lot...

29:18.883 --> 29:21.966
Whoa! Whoa!
Okay, there it is.

29:28.935 --> 29:30.300
Mm. Mm. Mm.

29:30.478 --> 29:32.059
Lisa. Lisa. I can't.

29:32.230 --> 29:33.185
I can't!

29:34.023 --> 29:37.390
-Sarah...
-Sarah is dragging you down.

29:37.860 --> 29:39.396
Just like...

29:39.570 --> 29:41.401
Alison was.

29:42.490 --> 29:44.321
I'm gonna walk you back
to your hotel.

29:44.492 --> 29:45.527
Okay?

29:45.993 --> 29:47.244
You know I'm right.

29:48.663 --> 29:51.575
You use Sarah,
but she used you right back.

29:51.958 --> 29:53.619
It's like when
somebody's drowning.

29:54.085 --> 29:56.747
You try and keep 'em afloat
for a while, but...

29:57.255 --> 29:58.495
before you know it,

29:58.506 --> 30:01.213
you're both...
sinking into the mud.

30:01.801 --> 30:03.632
[ Phone rings ]

30:07.014 --> 30:07.799
[ Sighs ]

30:07.974 --> 30:08.759
Hello?

30:09.058 --> 30:11.094
Dylan, have you heard
from Sarah?

30:11.519 --> 30:13.350
No, I thought she was with you.

30:13.646 --> 30:15.261
DYLAN: What's going on?

30:15.648 --> 30:17.309
Just meet me at the station.

30:19.986 --> 30:21.192
What is it, The Executioner?

30:21.362 --> 30:22.442
I gotta go.

30:24.949 --> 30:26.064
Hey...

30:26.867 --> 30:28.368
When this story is done...

30:28.953 --> 30:29.738
I'm gone.

30:44.802 --> 30:46.258
You ever go camping,
growing up?

30:46.429 --> 30:47.214
[ Chuckles ]

30:47.388 --> 30:48.548
Camping with Brenda?

30:49.056 --> 30:50.136
[ Laughs ]

30:50.141 --> 30:51.130
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

30:51.142 --> 30:52.473
No, she did send me
to camp once, though.

30:52.727 --> 30:53.967
Camp Motega.

30:56.522 --> 30:57.432
I'm surprised.

30:57.440 --> 30:58.270
Well, you know.

30:58.524 --> 31:00.640
Cam was a counselor there,
so she knew I'd be safe.

31:00.985 --> 31:01.770
Yeah.

31:03.321 --> 31:04.151
You know,

31:04.488 --> 31:06.194
up until then,
the only boats I had been on

31:06.198 --> 31:07.654
were the ones that take you
from one Caribbean island

31:07.658 --> 31:08.613
to another.

31:08.617 --> 31:09.606
-[ Laughs ]
-Right.

31:09.618 --> 31:10.528
So when I first got to camp,

31:10.536 --> 31:12.117
I headed straight
for the canoes

31:12.288 --> 31:13.653
and jumped in and...

31:14.540 --> 31:16.201
You gotta keep
your center of gravity

31:16.208 --> 31:17.163
as low as possible.

31:17.335 --> 31:19.075
Yeah, you know,
walk along the main line.

31:19.086 --> 31:19.996
I know that now.

31:20.004 --> 31:21.289
-[ Laughs ]
-I learned it the hard way.

31:25.426 --> 31:27.417
I would have taught you
how to canoe.

31:28.179 --> 31:29.715
Tie a little paddle.

31:30.222 --> 31:31.302
Fish.

31:31.766 --> 31:33.552
How to start a campfire.

31:34.727 --> 31:35.933
[ Sighs ]

31:36.270 --> 31:37.680
That would've been nice.

31:39.315 --> 31:40.304
Yeah.

31:41.484 --> 31:43.099
Do you regret
coming back here?

31:44.653 --> 31:46.689
I thought if I could go back
and face the past,

31:46.864 --> 31:48.980
I could come out
the other side... home.

31:50.242 --> 31:52.233
Instead, I'm on the run
from a serial killer

31:52.244 --> 31:53.154
with a killer.

31:53.371 --> 31:54.406
So...

31:54.705 --> 31:57.412
-Well, when you put it that way.
-Yeah.

32:02.254 --> 32:03.869
Why did you kill them, Tom?

32:08.094 --> 32:09.174
Please, just tell me the truth.

32:09.178 --> 32:10.008
Don't!

32:10.721 --> 32:11.676
What are you so afraid of?

32:11.889 --> 32:12.878
I'm not afraid.

32:13.599 --> 32:15.385
I-- I told you what happened.

32:15.976 --> 32:17.386
You don't want to believe me,
then, fine.

32:17.603 --> 32:19.309
But I'm not gonna
sit here and...

32:19.313 --> 32:20.143
[ Groaning ]

32:21.899 --> 32:23.014
Tom?

32:24.735 --> 32:26.066
[ Gasping ]

32:26.278 --> 32:27.688
Okay. Wait, wait.

32:28.030 --> 32:30.237
I'm calling 911, okay?
Just...

32:30.241 --> 32:32.106
You're having a seizure.
You need medical help, okay?

32:32.493 --> 32:34.199
-91 1 OPERA TOR: 91 1.
-HeHo?

32:34.537 --> 32:35.322
Uh, yeah, see I was...

32:35.496 --> 32:36.406
TOM: No.

32:36.414 --> 32:37.369
-911 OPERATOR: Hello?
-What are you doing?

32:37.873 --> 32:39.033
[ Grunting ]

32:40.167 --> 32:40.952
[ Choking ]

32:41.419 --> 32:42.204
Tom?

32:42.586 --> 32:44.087
You need to get out of here.

32:44.296 --> 32:45.081
SARAH: Just...

32:45.297 --> 32:47.162
I'm gonna go find some help.

32:47.174 --> 32:48.505
He'll be able
to trace you now.

32:48.509 --> 32:49.749
Okay. Just wait here.

32:49.927 --> 32:50.677
Don't worry, right?

32:50.845 --> 32:51.755
-TOM: Don 't.
-Don 't?

32:52.012 --> 32:53.001
Okay.

32:53.222 --> 32:54.507
[ Choking ]

33:00.104 --> 33:02.436
You had one job,
to protect Sarah.

33:02.648 --> 33:04.263
You just let her walk off
with that monster.

33:05.234 --> 33:06.565
-This is not...
-Don't touch me.

33:06.569 --> 33:07.433
...gonna help.

33:07.445 --> 33:09.026
We need to focus
on finding Sarah.

33:09.655 --> 33:11.771
'Cause, yes,
Tom Winston is a monster.

33:12.241 --> 33:13.230
So where are they?

33:14.243 --> 33:15.198
Hold up, somewhere.

33:15.369 --> 33:16.358
Unless, they made it
to the highway,

33:16.370 --> 33:17.530
which I don't think is likely.

33:17.788 --> 33:19.403
We closed down every road
in and out of town

33:19.415 --> 33:20.746
the minute that Tom escaped.

33:20.916 --> 33:21.666
[ Phone rings ]

33:23.794 --> 33:24.829
Where?

33:25.004 --> 33:27.336
Just outside of town,
near Wannick Creek.

33:27.506 --> 33:29.246
There's no GPS,
so it's a broad area.

33:29.508 --> 33:31.794
Sharma, I want everyone out there
searching for Sarah and Tom.

33:31.969 --> 33:33.209
-Right now.
-Of course.

33:33.762 --> 33:34.592
Cam, let me help.

33:34.889 --> 33:37.096
I've got a car, good pair of eyes
for a guy my age.

33:37.099 --> 33:37.849
All right.

33:38.017 --> 33:39.177
-All right.
-But do not approach them.

33:39.435 --> 33:40.515
You see anything,
you call me?

33:40.519 --> 33:41.349
-Yeah.
-All right.

33:41.604 --> 33:42.434
I'm going, too.

33:42.730 --> 33:43.719
The same goes for you.

33:44.398 --> 33:46.138
You see them,
you contact me.

33:46.400 --> 33:47.810
-Understood?
-Yeah, chief.

33:48.527 --> 33:49.812
Understood.

34:00.915 --> 34:01.700
[Car braking ]

34:02.750 --> 34:03.535
Hey!

34:04.210 --> 34:05.416
Hey! Hel-- Help!

34:06.504 --> 34:07.835
[ Muffled screaming ]

34:11.050 --> 34:12.711
[ Saw revving up ]

34:16.764 --> 34:18.846
[ Groaning ]

34:20.851 --> 34:21.636
Sarah.

34:22.269 --> 34:23.475
Where are we?

34:25.314 --> 34:26.850
The punishment for pride...

34:28.234 --> 34:29.474
is being broken on the wheel.

34:35.032 --> 34:36.397
Why are you here?

34:36.659 --> 34:38.115
Why is she here?

34:39.537 --> 34:40.822
[ Saw revving down ]

34:45.417 --> 34:47.453
He has rules.

34:47.461 --> 34:48.621
What was your sin?

34:49.797 --> 34:51.003
TOM: Why don't you tell me?

34:53.968 --> 34:55.629
I tried to kill myself.

34:55.636 --> 34:56.876
Sarah.

34:57.263 --> 34:58.173
Why would you...?

34:58.180 --> 34:58.930
Why?

35:00.182 --> 35:01.297
Because of you.

35:03.811 --> 35:05.847
One night, I took some pills.

35:06.939 --> 35:08.554
Took a lot of pills.

35:14.154 --> 35:16.065
Sarah was playing God.

35:18.367 --> 35:19.948
And, yes, that is prideful.

35:20.536 --> 35:23.369
But it was a sin she committed
against herself, no one else.

35:24.290 --> 35:25.370
Let her go.

35:25.624 --> 35:26.488
Please.

35:41.557 --> 35:42.592
[ Screaming ]
No!

35:42.600 --> 35:43.555
No, goddamnit!

35:43.559 --> 35:44.514
No!

35:44.518 --> 35:45.507
-Let her go!
-No!

35:45.519 --> 35:46.304
Let her go!

35:46.520 --> 35:47.430
[ Screaming ]

35:47.438 --> 35:48.348
Take me!

35:49.940 --> 35:52.056
I'm the one
who deserves to die!

35:52.943 --> 35:56.356
TOM: I know change takes time,
but we are making a difference.

35:56.655 --> 35:59.067
-WOMAN: Yes.
-Galatians 6:9.

35:59.700 --> 36:02.988
"And let us not grow weary
of doing good,

36:03.162 --> 36:04.993
for in due season
we will reap

36:04.997 --> 36:06.783
if we do not give up."

36:06.957 --> 36:07.707
WOMAN: Amen.

36:07.958 --> 36:08.743
WOMAN 2: Amen.

36:09.376 --> 36:10.912
Do not listen...

36:11.712 --> 36:14.624
to the darkness that exists
in our world today.

36:15.799 --> 36:18.211
-[ Door opening ]
-Don't live your life...

36:19.720 --> 36:20.505
[ Door closing ]

36:23.474 --> 36:24.304
[ Sighs ]

36:24.850 --> 36:27.466
Uh, ma'am, you're a bit early.

36:27.895 --> 36:29.851
Uh, our evening service
does not start until...

36:30.522 --> 36:31.728
...8:30.

36:32.483 --> 36:33.268
Actually...

36:34.276 --> 36:37.313
I heard about what you did,
and it inspired me.

36:39.490 --> 36:40.354
Oh.

36:41.325 --> 36:43.862
Really, well, I'm--
I'm glad.

36:44.370 --> 36:45.576
I've seen what the drugs, and...

36:46.080 --> 36:48.867
prostitution and pornography's
clone to this town.

36:49.333 --> 36:50.618
It sickens me.

36:51.585 --> 36:52.700
I wanna help.

36:52.920 --> 36:54.410
In any way that I can.

36:58.842 --> 37:00.628
Please take a seat at the pew.

37:01.220 --> 37:02.460
And join us.

37:04.890 --> 37:07.472
TOM: Now, Alan Henry
is just a small part

37:07.476 --> 37:09.057
of a much bigger problem
in Waterbury.

37:09.228 --> 37:11.685
And...
[ Clears throat ]

37:12.773 --> 37:14.263
[ Sighs ]

37:16.902 --> 37:18.267
Uh...

37:19.405 --> 37:20.565
Where was I? Uh...

37:21.657 --> 37:22.487
TOM: Right.

37:22.908 --> 37:24.148
The sins of this town...

37:24.326 --> 37:26.066
Of which there are many.

37:34.878 --> 37:36.038
I should go.

37:36.338 --> 37:37.293
Hey.

37:37.673 --> 37:40.005
Bryan won't be back
until after dinner.

37:40.008 --> 37:41.214
[ Sighs ]

37:43.470 --> 37:44.676
[ Sighs ]

37:45.639 --> 37:46.754
RACHEL: Hey.

37:48.225 --> 37:49.431
What's going on?

37:51.061 --> 37:53.177
You're a married woman,
and it's wrong.

37:53.397 --> 37:54.477
It's-- It's sinful.

37:54.857 --> 37:55.892
It's fun.

37:56.525 --> 37:57.765
It's alive.

37:58.736 --> 38:00.101
It's magic.

38:00.571 --> 38:02.027
For both of us.

38:03.532 --> 38:04.317
I love you.

38:06.368 --> 38:07.198
I do.

38:08.120 --> 38:09.405
I love you, Rachel. And...

38:09.788 --> 38:11.699
I want to spend the rest
of my life with you.

38:11.707 --> 38:12.742
And we can.

38:13.292 --> 38:15.328
Leave Bryan.
Come with me.

38:15.544 --> 38:16.704
Oh, I know.

38:17.296 --> 38:18.832
How difficult this is for you.

38:19.131 --> 38:20.837
Tom, just stop.
Tom, please.

38:20.841 --> 38:23.378
You aren't
in impossible situation.

38:24.803 --> 38:27.920
But love... is not easy, Rachel.

38:27.931 --> 38:29.137
I can't.

38:29.308 --> 38:30.593
I can't do this anymore.

38:30.851 --> 38:32.933
You hear me?
I can't do this.

38:35.355 --> 38:36.481
[ Door opening ]

38:36.982 --> 38:37.937
It's okay.

38:38.358 --> 38:39.973
-Geez!
-BRYAN: Don 't get up.

38:41.028 --> 38:42.017
It's cool, man.

38:42.488 --> 38:43.318
It's cool.

38:43.572 --> 38:44.436
RacheL

38:44.907 --> 38:46.147
Why don't you go
wash him off you?

38:46.158 --> 38:47.773
I'll take care of this mess.

38:47.785 --> 38:48.900
Look".

38:49.661 --> 38:51.447
Bryan, I didn't want it--
I didn't want it to happen.

38:51.663 --> 38:53.324
I did-- I did...
We fell in love, and then...

38:53.499 --> 38:56.081
Okay, it's cool, man.
Just calm down, all right.

38:56.293 --> 38:57.874
-We're in love, and I...
-Tom! Tom!

38:58.128 --> 39:00.164
I told you, it's cool, man.

39:00.172 --> 39:02.709
Don't have a coronary.
Okay, look, here, I'm gonna...

39:03.050 --> 39:04.756
gonna turn around.

39:05.385 --> 39:07.046
You can put your clothes
back on, okay?

39:10.849 --> 39:11.929
So?

39:12.768 --> 39:13.723
-How was she?
-[ Shower running ]

39:14.436 --> 39:15.186
What?

39:15.354 --> 39:18.391
Rachel, in the sack, man.
Did you like being with her?

39:18.398 --> 39:19.353
I know you did, but what...

39:19.900 --> 39:21.481
What was your favorite part?

39:21.485 --> 39:22.520
Or should I say "parts"?

39:24.112 --> 39:25.568
I'm gonna--
I'm just-- I'm gonna go.

39:25.739 --> 39:26.899
No, you're not!

39:27.324 --> 39:28.109
Sit down.

39:28.617 --> 39:29.982
[ Shower running ]

39:29.993 --> 39:33.736
I... will tell you...
when you can go.

39:38.001 --> 39:39.332
So it's the boobs?

39:39.920 --> 39:42.627
Yeah, Rachel's got a great rack,
and they're natural, too.

39:42.631 --> 39:44.622
Which is very rare,
in this business.

39:47.010 --> 39:48.625
Business? What are you--?
What are you talking about?

40:00.524 --> 40:02.230
BRYAN:
You're a natural, too, Tom.

40:02.234 --> 40:05.226
Though, you might want
to tone down that love shit.

40:05.237 --> 40:06.022
[ Sighs ]

40:06.488 --> 40:08.103
My friend, um...

40:08.574 --> 40:09.859
Alan Henry?

40:10.951 --> 40:12.612
Yeah, he gets the videos
out there for us.

40:12.619 --> 40:13.950
He distributes them.

40:15.163 --> 40:17.245
But lately, you...
have been giving us

40:17.249 --> 40:18.864
a very hard time,
haven't you?

40:19.918 --> 40:22.034
I'm doing...
I'm doing God's work.

40:23.714 --> 40:24.578
ReaHy?

40:24.923 --> 40:26.163
[ Chuckling ]

40:26.383 --> 40:27.133
This...

40:27.301 --> 40:29.007
...is God's work, Tom, huh?

40:29.636 --> 40:31.422
BRYAN: Okay, so here's
how it's gonna go down.

40:32.097 --> 40:33.507
Rachel and me...

40:34.433 --> 40:36.389
We're gonna keep this
between the three of us.

40:36.852 --> 40:38.638
And all you gotta do...

40:40.314 --> 40:41.895
is stop getting in the way.

40:45.319 --> 40:46.104
BRYAN: Great.

40:46.320 --> 40:47.230
Thank you, Tom.

40:49.406 --> 40:51.943
I have... one last question
for you.

40:54.494 --> 40:56.485
All that love stuff
with Rachel...

40:58.040 --> 40:59.780
Did you really mean that?

41:03.670 --> 41:05.046
Yeah.

41:06.131 --> 41:07.246
All of it.

41:07.925 --> 41:09.836
[ Slicing sounds ]

41:10.260 --> 41:11.716
So says the Lord.

41:12.095 --> 41:13.005
[ Distorted voice ]
Says the Lord.

41:13.013 --> 41:13.798
Righteous.

41:14.181 --> 41:16.297
"And deliver from the hand
of the oppressor

41:16.308 --> 41:18.264
him who has been robbed."

41:18.518 --> 41:19.769
[ Distorted voice ]
Robbed. Robbed.

41:20.228 --> 41:23.061
"You're shed blood
of the innocent."

41:23.065 --> 41:24.271
[ Distorted voice ]
Innocent blood.

41:24.983 --> 41:25.768
Innocent.

41:26.276 --> 41:27.482
Innocent.

41:27.945 --> 41:29.105
[ Distorted voice ]
Execute.

41:29.112 --> 41:31.728
"I will execute great vengeance
on them

41:31.740 --> 41:33.025
with wrathful rebukes."

41:33.033 --> 41:33.863
[ Distorted ] Wrathful rebukes.
Wrathful rebukes.

41:34.034 --> 41:37.151
As Christians, it is our duty,

41:37.704 --> 41:38.739
our burden,

41:40.457 --> 41:43.665
to take action against sin,
wherever we may find it.

41:45.003 --> 41:46.868
I wasn't doing God's work.

41:47.464 --> 41:50.080
There was no higher purpose.
It was my ego.

41:50.342 --> 41:52.799
My wounded pride
that drove me to murder them.

41:54.096 --> 41:55.336
You don't need to do this.

41:55.973 --> 41:57.554
You can let her go!

41:57.724 --> 41:59.225
[ Heavy breathing ]

42:04.147 --> 42:04.977
[ Screaming ]

42:06.400 --> 42:08.061
No! Goddamnit!

42:08.360 --> 42:09.145
[ Grunting ]

42:16.368 --> 42:17.198
[ Choking ]

42:17.411 --> 42:20.073
Please tell me,
I'm the sinner.

42:20.080 --> 42:21.160
Take me.

42:22.416 --> 42:24.452
Let me die for her!

42:31.174 --> 42:31.959
[ Whimpering ]

42:33.552 --> 42:35.543
[ Saw revving down ]

42:38.265 --> 42:39.801
Now, let her go!

42:52.195 --> 42:53.651
[ Regular voice ]
EXECUTIONER: I let her go.

42:56.158 --> 42:57.318
What?

42:58.326 --> 42:59.782
You don't have to do this.

43:00.412 --> 43:01.401
Yes.

43:02.122 --> 43:03.328
I do.

43:04.458 --> 43:05.664
I love you, Sarah.

43:18.680 --> 43:21.262
Give me your word,
no harm will come to her.

43:29.608 --> 43:30.939
Then, I'm ready.

43:41.912 --> 43:43.777
Now, get her out of here.

43:43.789 --> 43:45.029
SARAH: No.

43:45.707 --> 43:47.413
I'm not leaving you
to die alone.

44:29.709 --> 44:30.835
MAN: Excuse me,
coming through.

44:31.128 --> 44:32.038
You guys.
Sarah. Sarah.

44:32.045 --> 44:33.455
Are you okay?
Did he hurt you?

44:33.463 --> 44:34.543
SARAH: You stay away
from me, okay?

44:34.548 --> 44:35.833
-What do you mean, Sarah?
-You stay the hell away from me!

44:35.841 --> 44:36.876
You lying bastard!

44:36.883 --> 44:38.464
Hey! Back off, Bennett!

44:47.269 --> 44:49.055
[ Birds chirping ]

44:56.278 --> 44:59.145
[ Birds chirping ]

45:13.420 --> 45:14.876
[ Sighs ]

45:16.089 --> 45:17.454
[ Coughs ]

45:26.933 --> 45:28.469
[ Birds chirping ]

45:52.083 --> 45:53.209
[ Gasps ]

45:54.502 --> 45:56.663
[ Police siren wailing ]

46:04.262 --> 46:06.173
[ Police sirens continue ]

46:13.521 --> 46:14.931
Sarah, get back!

46:15.357 --> 46:16.312
Sarah!

46:16.316 --> 46:17.476
CAM: Stop!

46:27.953 --> 46:29.864
Sarah, don't touch it.
That's evidence.

46:34.042 --> 46:35.202
[ Tearing envelope ]

46:40.173 --> 46:43.336
"The righteous will rejoice
when he sees the vengeance;

46:43.635 --> 46:46.047
he will wash his feet
in the blood of the wicked,

46:46.263 --> 46:50.176
and men will say, "Surely, there
is a reward for the righteous;

46:50.600 --> 46:53.182
surely there is a God
who judges on Earth."

46:56.231 --> 46:57.767
He thinks this is over.

46:59.359 --> 47:01.520
It's not even close
to being over.

47:11.705 --> 47:12.820
Good morning.

47:14.416 --> 47:16.577
And what a beautiful
morning it is.

47:17.127 --> 47:18.583
It's like when a storm
has passed

47:18.586 --> 47:20.122
and everything
is bright and new.

47:21.506 --> 47:24.339
Uh, I'm gonna grab a couple
of hours of shut-eye.

47:25.343 --> 47:26.549
It's over, Cam.

47:27.137 --> 47:29.048
This town has been cleansed.

47:29.597 --> 47:31.133
And the Lord said in His heart,

47:34.144 --> 47:36.226
Nor will I again destroy
every living thing

47:36.229 --> 47:37.093
as I have done."

47:38.565 --> 47:40.226
Amen.
